Remove the double quotes around the column names, and use single quotes for the string literals:

&lt;!-- language: sql --&gt;

    INSERT INTO admin (ADMIN_CODE, DEPT_CODE, ID)
    VALUES
        (&#39;xxx&#39;, &#39;yyy&#39;, 1);

Actually on MySQL/MariaDB either double quotes or backticks should be legal for escaping a column name.  But in your case, you don&#39;t need escaping, so don&#39;t use double quotes.

